description:
Implement Focusa outage passthrough in Pi extension.

FILE: ~/.pi/agent/extensions/focusa-pi-bridge.ts

IN EVERY Focusa API call, wrap with:
  try {
    const res = await fetch(url, { signal: AbortSignal.timeout(2000) });
    if (!res.ok) throw new Error(res.status);
    return await res.json();
  } catch (e) {
    ctx.ui.notify('Focusa unavailable — passthrough mode', 'warn');
    return null;  // caller skips Focusa features
  }

AUTO-RECONNECT:
  let focusaDown = false;
  let reconnectAttempt = 0;

  On failure: focusaDown = true, reconnectAttempt++
  Every 30s while focusaDown: try GET :8787/v1/health
    If success: focusaDown = false, reconnectAttempt = 0, ctx.ui.notify('Focusa reconnected')
  Backoff: Math.min(30 * 2^reconnectAttempt, 300) seconds

SOFT RESYNC on reconnect:
  Fetch /v1/focus/stack, /v1/constitution/active to restore cached state

VERIFY: Kill Focusa, Pi continues working. Restart Focusa, Pi reconnects within 60s.
REF: doc 44 §11

Persist Focusa/WBM state in Pi session via appendEntry.

FILE: ~/.pi/agent/extensions/focusa-pi-bridge.ts
API: pi.appendEntry('focusa-wbm-state', data)

SAVE (on WBM toggle, periodic, session_shutdown):
  pi.appendEntry('focusa-wbm-state', {
    sessionId: focusaSessionId,
    frameId: activeFrameId,
    wbmEnabled: wbmEnabled,
    cataloguedDecisions: [...localDecisions],
    cataloguedFacts: [...cataloguedFacts],
    timestamp: Date.now()
  });

RESTORE (on session_start):
  for (const entry of ctx.sessionManager.getEntries()) {
    if (entry.type === 'custom' && entry.customType === 'focusa-wbm-state') {
      // Use LAST entry (most recent state)
      restore from entry.data
    }
  }

ALSO: On resume, reconnect to saved Focusa session (§36.4, focusa-nh1d)
VERIFY: /wbm on → exit → /resume → WBM auto-enabled, decisions restored.
REF: doc 44 §33.7, §36.4

