Add procedural rule removal threshold.

FILE: /home/wirebot/focusa/crates/focusa-core/src/memory/procedural.rs
FUNCTION: decay_tick()

CURRENT: weight *= decay_factor every 30s, but rules never removed.

ADD after decay loop:
  // Remove dead rules (weight below threshold for 7+ days)
  memory.procedural.retain(|rule| {
    if rule.weight < 0.01 {
      // Check if below threshold for 7+ days
      let days_below = (Utc::now() - rule.last_reinforced_at).num_days();
      if days_below > 7 { return false; }  // Remove
    }
    if rule.weight < 0.1 {
      let days_below = (Utc::now() - rule.last_reinforced_at).num_days();
      if days_below > 30 { return false; }  // Remove dormant rules
    }
    true
  });

NOTE: May need to add last_reinforced_at field to RuleRecord if not present.
CHECK: grep 'last_reinforced' crates/focusa-core/src/types.rs

BUILD: cargo build --release
TEST: cargo test --workspace
VERIFY: Create a rule with low weight. Wait for decay. Confirm removal after threshold.
REF: UNIFIED_ORGANISM_SPEC §10.4
